definitions.definition: A class of tetraterpene plant pigments ; they vary in colour from yellow , through orange to red , this colour originating in a chain of alternating single and double bonds .
Specifically, a number of isomers of tetraterpene hydrocarbons , C 40 H 56 , (especially beta-carotene ), present in carrots etc, which are converted into vitamin A in the liver .
